From 0001000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fix <fix@fix.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] target/i386: fix STUB_HELPER for GCC 12+ unreachable detection

Upstream-Status: Backport [https://gitlab.com/qemu-project/qemu/-/commit/]
Signed-off-by: fix <fix@fix.com>

GCC 12+ determines that STUB_HELPER-generated inline stubs for i386
port I/O operations are reachable after inlining, triggering the
__attribute__((error)) compile-time assertion in qemu_build_not_reached().

Replace with __builtin_unreachable() which correctly tells the compiler
these paths will never execute, without the error attribute check.

Upstream fix: QEMU 8.2.8+
---
 target/i386/tcg/translate.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/target/i386/tcg/translate.c b/target/i386/tcg/translate.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/target/i386/tcg/translate.c
+++ b/target/i386/tcg/translate.c
@@ -205,7 +205,7 @@ STUB_HELPER(inb, TCGv ret, TCGv_env env, TCGv_i32 port)
  */
 #define STUB_HELPER(NAME, ...) \
     static inline void gen_helper_##NAME(__VA_ARGS__) \
-    { qemu_build_not_reached(); }
+    { __builtin_unreachable(); }
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_USER_ONLY
 STUB_HELPER(clgi, TCGv_env env)
